	-- Scales the whole panel relative to a reference viewport height so it stays
	-- readable (and doesn't overflow) on smaller phone/tablet screens, and doesn't
	-- balloon oversized on ultra-high-res monitors either. UIScale doesn't change
	-- any of the Offset/Scale math used elsewhere (dragging, layout, etc.), it just
	-- visually scales the whole subtree, so nothing else needs to change.
	local MainScale = Instance.new("UIScale")
